JOS – Deputy Speaker of the House of Representatives, Ahmed Idris Wase, has felicitated with the Muslim Ummah on the occasion of Eid el-Kabir Sallah celebration. In his Sallah message to Muslims issued by his Chief Press Secretary, Umar Muhammad Puma and made available to Daily Independent, Wase called on Muslims to use the period to offer prayers for the unity and progress of the country. The Deputy Speaker said peaceful co-existence and understanding, as well as sustained prayers among citizens, were essential in the face of the current economic and security challenges in the country. He stated: “As we celebrate this year’s Eid-El-Fitri, let us put our country and its leadership in our prayers. Eid-el-Kabir celebration is a period of sacrifice and reflection.I urge us all to emulate the virtues of total obedience and sacrifice.